  "text": "Deletion mutants in genes involved in iron uptake and metabolism were constructed by using lambda Red methodology [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . ⌬iroN, ⌬fepA, and ⌬entC mutants of background strain 14028 were generated previously by using a similar methodology [CITATION_3] , and the ⌬fepB mutant was generated in this study by using primers fepB fwd (5=-GCGCTAACC TAAGAGTAAAACGTCGCTCTGTCAACTGTGTAGGCTGGAGCTGC TTC-3=) and fepB rev (5=-AATCGGTCTGGTCAGTCGGATAAGACTC CGATAAGGCATATGAATATCCTCCTTAG-3=). PCR confirmed the insertion of the cassette by using site-specific and internal kanamycin primers. P22 phage lysates were prepared from each mutant strain and used to transduce each mutation into wild-type strain SL1344.",
